text: Towson () is an unincorporated community and a census-designated place in Baltimore County, Maryland. The population was 59,553 at the 2020 census. It is the county seat, and the second-most populated unincorporated county seat in the United States. ==References== Category:Census-designated places in Maryland Category:County seats in Maryland Category:Unincorporated communities in Maryland
title: Towson, Maryland
